  "title": "Maintenance Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee and coordinate all maintenance works, including troubleshooting, ensuring tasks are completed safely, effectively, and on schedule.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with the Maintenance Manager to plan and execute breakdown, preventive, and shutdown maintenance schedules and budgets.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate daily maintenance activities with the Production team and conduct daily toolbox meetings.</li>\n  <li>Inspect sites regularly to identify maintenance needs, potential issues, and improvement opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Conduct risk assessment reviews with contractors to ensure compliance with safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with professional engineers and service providers for statutory equipment inspections and testing.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with all health, safety, and environmental regulations, and work with management to address and resolve any issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Maintenance related field</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years’ experience</li>\n  <li>Fresh Graduates are welcomed</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click on the APPLY button below to send in your resume.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 13C6305</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Reg. No.: R22104949 KOH SHI MIN, JOAN (XU SHIMIN)</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>For candidates who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
